br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23310.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> I think that you raise good points but your basis is skewed.</span><hr size=1> Those are in fact the two main kinds of encounters, but what you're missing here, in my opinion, is that the different types of encounters, in essence, require the same man hours for the same loot.  And this basic fact promotes ALL players to be able to gain loot depending on their social preferences.<br><br>These type 2 encounters you speak of allow for similar quality loot from smaller groups.  Plane of Sky isnt as good an example, b/c it is an old zone that has been sparsely updated beyond quest endings, but it still fits the pattern.  Plane of Mischeif is the poster child for this type of encounter.  PoM can be cleared by 2 people if they're good enough, and by almost ANY full group.  Yes it takes more time for those ppl, but what you're missing is this.<br><br>Type 1<br>30ppl * 4hours = 120 man hours total.<br>Type 2<br>2ppl * 60 hours = 120 man hours total.<br><br>Not to mention that in PoM you can have multiple chars played by a single person to, in effect, make it a MORE efficient encounter in the end.  To you, being in a Type 1 capable guild, may not appreciate the value of that.  Lately I've no need for that kind of activity, but at one point in time I was uncomfortable with all &quot;high-end&quot; guilds/sects on my server.  Instead, 5 friends and I all created our own little guild and spent a great deal of time looking for anything that one perfect group could accomplish.  At that time, post-K/pre-V, there wasnt much in the way of that type, but we found things to get into anyway.  Had there been a PoM at that point in time we'd have been in heaven.<br><br>Tho I no longer look for single group raid encounter style play, I know there must still be people in those situations out there.  Whether they're just at odds with said uber-guild or whether they have odd, unreliable, play schedules or just wont join a larger guild for any reason, I feel that PoM style encounters are very valuable to the &quot;average&quot; high end player.  So its not FOR everyone, granted, but what you miss when you get entrenched in NTOV/AoW style events is that those arent for everyone either.  <br><br>I think the best possible answer to this would be that type 2 encounters be refined to limit involvement to only one group.  Have a zone max or say make a zone only accessible to one group at a time.  Problematic for sure, but if we're speaking in the hypothetical here lets propose solutions other than, please dont do this again.  I say do it again, but do it right.<br>If PoM were a zone, accessible other than NToV, and limited to no more than 6 ppl at a time, perhaps even with a single point of entry, so that only one group could, 'port' in at a time, similiar to the luclin ports, it would be far more effective.  Then the card drops could be set back a bit, to slightly more common than now and not have the capability of being a open floodgate.<br><br>Awaiting Feedback,<br><br>Vanessalynne<br>Rallos Zek Assassin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dunkelheit>Dunkelheit</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/18/02 7:47:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23310.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> one question</span><hr size=1> I would like to ask one question:<br><br>WHY do you all go to &quot;raids&quot;.... is it fun? Or is it loot at the end?<br><br>I think all take the mindnumbingly boring encounters just to get loot. And this cannot be right.... I want fun dammit.<br><br>Take the Rogue epic for example.... it is FUN, it is mostly doable by yourself..... the plane of hate trip is plain awesome if you do it yourself. <br><br>Why must all quests be <br>a) a super rare spawn with a super rare drop required, which adds up to a super super super rare item...<br><br>or<br>b) need at least 150 super equipped lvl 60 with at least 100 aaexp points <br><br>????<br><br>Why aren't there more quests than the rogue epic?<br><br>I play a necro as a main.... where is the fun in doing fear 50 times and still see no slimeblood drop?<br><br>A very good feature would be, that only one group is allowed to zone in at a time.... and if you have gone beyond a trigger door or something, you cannot go back and the next group is allowed to port in. So you have some other option than the 2 damn boring options above.<br><br>And please... remove the no drop thingy... let the economy roll. So that casual players can get good loot. <br><br>And please.... make the trade skills useful....  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showPrevMessage?topicID=23310.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showNextMessage?topicID=23310.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23310.topic&index=6><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.emailToFriend?topicID=23310.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Ema